comment: Korver (ATL) is standing in bounds when he sets the screen on Williams (LAL).
Korver (ATL) makes incidental contact with Young (LAL) that does not affect his FOM off the ball.
Howard (ATL) sets the screen on Young (LAL) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Nance Jr. (LAL) sets the screen on Schroder (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Millsap (ATL) establishes legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Nance Jr. (LAL).
Randle (LAL) makes contact with Schroder's (ATL) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Millsap (ATL) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically as he contests Russell's (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Nance Jr. (LAL) cleanly knocks the ball away from Sefolosha (ATL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the time on the game clock was confirmed.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by LAL was upheld.
Randle (LAL) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Schroder (ATL).
Randle (LAL) makes contact with the ball before it touches the backboard.
Schroder (ATL) makes incidental contact with Russell (LAL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Howard (ATL) sets the screen on Russell (LAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Randle (LAL) and Howard (ATL) briefly engage and separate in the paint.
[Incidental or immaterial] Howard (ATL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
